scription>? We were able to confirm the role of ECM in synaptic adhesion at the Drosophila NMJ and were able to pinpoint this as an indirect role mediated through basement membrane adhesion.



? We established a list of 285 adhesion factors through in silico searches, and carried out detailed ultrastructural analyses of 18 genotypes selected through in silico and literature searches; none of these factors showed an obvious detachment phenotype.



? We carried out combinations of loss of functions of adhesion factors to an unprecedented degree, including complete deletion of classical cadherins, flamingo-type cadherins and neurexins at the NMJ. We did not find any enhanced detachment - leading to the key statement that synaptic adhesion is redundant to such a degree that future studies at any synapse are highly unlikely to ever produce a detachment phenotype.</gtr:description><gtr:id>5783B015-8CF8-444C-A952-F3A1DCB9C071</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Agriculture/ Food and Drink</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/7A48BEBB-C489-4E9E-999D-8E53A5A8F90D"><gtr:id>7A48BEBB-C489-4E9E-999D-8E53A5A8F90D</gtr:id><gtr:title>Regulation of microtubule networks in neuronal growth</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/66900d06b55f9ed50af7d1b1eb9142a4"><gtr:id>66900d06b55f9ed50af7d1b1eb9142a4</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Andreas Prokop (Author)</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/B7FF368F-351C-4867-B3AF-2C8DA8E51C7C"><gtr:id>B7FF368F-351C-4867-B3AF-2C8DA8E51C7C</gtr:id><gtr:title>Ultrastructure and regulation of adhesion at a genetically tractable model synapse</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/d12b5e5f1cae877b54d6e27876e38fb8"><gtr:id>d12b5e5f1cae877b54d6e27876e38fb8</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Koper Prokop (Author)</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2009-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/D874B3EE-A017-4E6C-9EAA-B6283D82D851"><gtr:id>D874B3EE-A017-4E6C-9EAA-B6283D8